content.description: Climb up easy moves to the top of the ramp.  Take a breath, adjust your tie, and get ready for the business to start.  Big moves on positive edges lead to a spicy finish!
content.location: This is the first sport route to the right of the twin cracks.

content.description: Very gradual and blocky climb up to a two bolt anchor
content.location: right of the prominent arete at the right hand side of unemployment wall.

content.description:
Note!  The name is a placeholder, in keeping with the Rabbit Hole theme, and with a nod to the Lewis Carroll wall nextdoor. It was more fun than "Unknown," for now, and the actual route name correction is welcome.

This line goes up the right side face of the Rabbit Hole arete.  It's thin and covered in lichen.
content.location: Right of the Down the Rabbit Hole arete

content.description: moderate climbing to a tricky move off the ramp.
content.location: This route is the furthest to the right on the unemployment wall.  It is on a rocky ledge just before the trail heads towards the river and emerges into a boulder field.

content.description: fingers to hand sized crack.  Bring tape for the popcorn near the top... or neosporin.  Climb the back of the large boulder to gain the ramp and the start. short.
content.protection:
Cams from fingers to hands. An experienced leader could get by with a single rack however a double set is useful.

Make sure to bring at least 2x #2 and 2x#1
content.location: This is the crack to the right of the horizontal finger crack, they share the same starting point. Starts on a large flake like thing with a wide finger crack on the left and a #4 - #5 camalot underneath.  I found it easiest just to face climb this feature rather than crack climb it.

content.description: Delicate moves on slopers at the bottom leads to easier climbing up top
content.location: to the right of Becky Hole

content.description: a mixture of strong and delicate moves lead up this beautiful arete.
content.protection: 10 bolts to hangers.  A couple long draws or slings would be helpful to top rope.
content.location: climbs the obvious arete to the right of sexual harassment.

content.description: Hand crack with popcorn to shared chains. tape up!
content.protection: two bolts project the easy face climbing to the ramp.
content.location: just to the right of the 'cave' and the large boulder there is a twin crack system with a pillar of sorts in the middle.  This is the rightmost crack.

content.description: climbs a broken pillar inside a crack to the ramp.  Move left and up to holds at a small roof. Move through the crux on small holes and ledges then straight up to the chains.
content.location: one route to the right of welcome to unemployment.

content.description: Beautiful line with a hard start and an inspiring finish!
content.location: To the right of Fondling Firm.  Starts in a shallow dihedral on a thin tan plate/crack then moves into a wider sharp layback before pulling a bulge.
